http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/Seer-to-visit-Ongole-on-Sunday/article13996166.ece

Tridandi Srimannarayana Chinna Jeeyar Swami will visit Ongole on Sunday in connection with the 1,000th birth anniversary of Sri Ramanujacharya falling next year. The pontiff will lead the ‘Vishnu Nama’ recitation at the Tata Lakshmiprasad Kalyana Mandam here, according to Vikas Tarangini president T. Hariprasad. He will seek support from the public for the construction of a 216-ft ‘Statue of Equality’, costing over Rs. 600 crore, as part of the millennium celebrations, at Muchintal on the outskirts of Hyderabad.